Canada’s New Democratic Party Chooses Turmel to Stand In for Ailing Layton

-- B y   T h e o p h i l o s   A r g i t i s
-- 
2011-07-28T15:28:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-28/canada-s-new-democratic-party-chooses-turmel-to-stand-in-for-ailing-layton.html
Canada ’s  New Democratic Party , the
country’s largest opposition party, has chosen Nycole Turmel as
interim leader.  Turmel, who spoke to reporters at a press conference in
Ottawa today, is standing in for  Jack Layton , who stepped aside
earlier this week for health reasons. Layton said he hopes to
return in September.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Theophilos Argitis in Ottawa at 
 targitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Badertscher at 
 pbadertscher@bloomberg.net  